HEADWORD: Navvy
<hw>Nav"vy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Navies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Abbreviated fr.
<ets>navigator</ets>.]</ety> <def>Originally, a laborer on canals for
internal navigation; hence, a laborer on other public works, as in
building railroads, embankments, etc.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

